<inglise> ANNEX </inglise>
<eesti> LISA </eesti>
<inglise> In order to be officially approved, breeders' associations and breeding organizations which maintain or establish a herd-book must: </inglise>
<eesti> T&otilde;uraamatut pidav v&otilde;i asutav t&otilde;uaretus&uuml;hing v&otilde;i -organisatsioon peab ametlikuks tunnustamiseks: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. have legal personality in accordance with the legislation in force in the Member State where the application is made; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) olema juriidiline isik vastavalt selle liikmesriigi kehtivatele &otilde;igusnormidele, kus tunnustamist taotletakse; </eesti>
<inglise> 2. prove to the competent authorities: </inglise>
<eesti> 2) t&otilde;endama p&auml;devale ametiasutusele, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) that they operate efficiently; </inglise>
<eesti> a) ta on v&otilde;imeline t&otilde;husalt t&ouml;&ouml;tama; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) that they can carry out the checks necessary for recording pedigrees; </inglise>
<eesti> b) ta on v&otilde;imeline tegema vajalikku kontrolli p&otilde;lvnemise registreerimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) that they have a sufficiently large herd to carry out a breed improvement programme, or that they have a sufficiently large herd to preserve the breed where this is considered necessary; </inglise>
<eesti> c) tal on piisavalt suur kari t&otilde;uparandusprogrammi teostamiseks v&otilde;i tal on piisavalt suur kari t&otilde;u s&auml;ilitamiseks, kui see on vajalik; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) that they can make use of the livestock performance data necessary for carrying out their breed improvement or preservation programme; </inglise>
<eesti> d) ta saab kasutada t&otilde;uparandus- v&otilde;i s&auml;ilitusprogrammi teostamiseks vajalikke eluskarja j&otilde;udluse andmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> 3. have a set of rules covering: </inglise>
<eesti> 3. omama reeglistikku, mis h&otilde;lmab: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the definition of the breed's (or breeds') characteristics; </inglise>
<eesti> a) t&otilde;u (v&otilde;i t&otilde;ugude) omaduste m&auml;&auml;ratlemist; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the system for identifying animals; </inglise>
<eesti> b) loomade identifitseerimiss&uuml;steemi; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the system for recording pedigrees; </inglise>
<eesti> c) p&otilde;lvnemise registreerimise s&uuml;steemi; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) the definition of their breeding objectives; </inglise>
<eesti> d) t&otilde;uaretuse eesm&auml;rkide m&auml;&auml;ratlemist; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) the systems for making use of livestock performance data, enabling the genetic value of the animals to be assessed; </inglise>
<eesti> e) eluskarja j&otilde;udluse andmete kasutamise s&uuml;steemi, mis v&otilde;imaldab hinnata loomade aretusv&auml;&auml;rtust; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) the division of the herd-book, if there are different conditions for entering animals or if there are different procedures for classifying the animals entered in the book; </inglise>
<eesti> f) t&otilde;uraamatu alamjaotust, kui on erinevad tingimused loomade t&otilde;uraamatusse kandmiseks v&otilde;i erinevad menetlused t&otilde;uraamatusse kantud loomade klassifitseerimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> 4. have articles of association, laying down, in particular, the principle of non-discrimination between members. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) omama p&otilde;hikirja, milles s&auml;testatakse eriti liikmete vahelise mittediskrimineerimise p&otilde;him&otilde;te. </eesti>
 